<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Auction,80</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>20-Day Bills Yield 7.93 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields averaged 7.93 percent on 20-day cash
management bills in the Treasury Department's latest auction.
   The discount rate understates the actual return to investors:
8.08 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,955.90.
   A total of $10.1 billion in bills were sold Tuesday out of bids
totaling $40.6 billion.
   The Treasury sells cash management bills at irregular intervals
and with varying terms to smooth out government cash flow.
