<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Nielsens     08-31 0335</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Nielsens,0345</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Emmys Highest Rated Show Yet for Fox</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Emmys show was fledgling Fox Broadcasting
Co.'s highest-rated ever even though it was the second lowest-rated
Emmys presentations, according to A.C. Nielsen Co. figures.
   ``The 40th Annual Emmy Awards'' broadcast Sunday ranked 33rd
among network shows with a rating of 10.4 and an 18 share, Fox's
highest showing among the networks.
   NBC won the night with ``Police Academy 2: First Assignment.''
Fox also trailed CBS' ``Blood and Orchids, Part 1,'' but that
didn't faze Fox President Jamie Kellner.
   ``I'm very pleased to be the No. 3 network nationally,'' he
said. ``I also think that we put a great show on.
   ``It's the first time we've ever over-delivered for advertisers,
so it was good for them, too,'' Kellner said. He said Fox had
guaranteed a 10.0 rating. Last year's Emmys was the lowest-rated
ever with an 8.8 its first of three years on Fox. When NBC carried
the Emmys in 1986, it got a rating of 23.7 and a 36 share.
   Otherwise, it was a week of reruns with NBC's ``The Cosby Show''
back in first place.
   The rest of the top 10 included NBC's ``A Different World,''
``Cheers'' and ``Night Court,'' CBS' ``60 Minutes'' and ``Murder,
She Wrote,'' NBC's ``Police Academy 2,'' ``Golden Girls,'' ``Amen''
and ``Hunter.''
   NBC won the week that ended Sunday with an average, prime-time
rating of 12.2. CBS had a 9.7 and ABC had 8.9. But the
three-network share of 56 percent was a rebound from the all-time
low 47 during the week of the Republican National Convention.
   Each rating point represents the antion's 886,000 households
with televisions. The share is a percentage of sets in use.
   In the evening news race, ``ABC World News Tonight'' pulled into
the lead with a 9.3 rating and 20 share. The ``CBS Evening News''
was second with a 9.0 and 20. ``NBC Nightly News'' remained in
third with an 8.6 and 18 share.
</TEXT>
