<HEAD>More Americans Behind in Mortgage Payments</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More Americans fell behind in their mortgage
payments in the April-June quarter, according to an organization of
lenders.
   The Mortgage Bankers Association of America said Tuesday that
the number of homeowners who were at least 30 days late in making a
mortgage payment edged up to 4.90 percent of the 9.8 million
mortgages surveyed in the second quarter.
