<HEAD>Nurses Group Endorses Dukakis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A national association of nurses is endorsing
Democrat Michael Dukakis for president.
   The American Nurses' Association, which says it represents the
more than 2 million registered nurses in the United States, says
one out of every 44 registered women voters is a nurse.
   Irene Agnos, chairwoman of the group's political action
committee, said the positions of Dukakis and running mate Sen.
Lloyd Bentsen on health care issues were a key factor in the
endorsement.
   ``We think that as president, Dukakis will make a difference for
this country and for health care consumers, and we look forward to
making a difference in his campaign,'' said Lucille Joel, nurses
association president.
   The organization in 1985 decided it would endorse a presidential
candidate after interviewing both major party candidates.
Association officials recently met with Dukakis, but Republican
George Bush declined their invitation to be interviewed, according
to an association news release.
