<HEAD>Thieves Drive Van Through Store Window, Steal Furs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thieves made off with ``as many furs as they
could carry'' from a Manhattan furrier after driving a van through
the store's front window early today, police said.
   The robbers drove the stolen van into the front window of
Antonovich Furs, ``ran into the store and grabbed as many furs as
they could carry'' and escaped with two other men waiting outside
in a car, said Sgt. Ed Burns, a police spokesman.
   There was no immediate estimate on the value of the furs taken
in the 4:30 a.m. heist, Burns said.
