<HEAD>First Miss America Contestant Arrives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>POMONA, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The first contestant in this year's Miss
America Pageant arrived in Atlantic City this morning with about 20
pieces of luggage.
   ``Last week I reported that I'd only have eight,'' Miss New York
Mia Seminoff said with a grin.
   The 23-year-old Manhattan resident arrived on a small plane at
the Atlantic City Airport here at 7:30 a.m. Five pageant hostesses
fought off yawns while waiting to greet her.
   ``This is the earliest I ever remember anyone arriving,'' said
hostess Millie Frambe.
   Miss Seminoff said the early arrival hour made sense. ``Now we
have the day in front of us to settle down and try to relax,'' she
said.
   Miss Seminoff was the first of 51 women who will arrive
Wednesday and Thursday in the seaside resort to compete for the
title of Miss America on Sept. 10.
   The contestants are arriving earlier than usual this year to
rehearse a more elaborate production number, pageant director
Leonard Horn said.
   Despite the early hour, Miss Seminoff happily posed for
photographers. When she realized that one button on her navy blue
and white linen dress had become undone, she quickly placed one
hand over the button hole and waved with the other.
