<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Nose Assailant,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Bites Man, Police Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STATESVILLE, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was arrested for allegedly biting
off part of another man's nose during a fight, authorities said.
   Brenton Cram, 24, of Statesville was arrested Tuesday as he
walked along Interstate 77 and was charged with the felony maiming
of Chris Hedrick.
   Cram, released on $5,500 secured bond, faces up to 10 years in
prison if convicted.
   Hedrick, 21, was in good condition Tuesday at Iredell Memorial
Hospital.
   Cram's estranged wife, Alisa Wise Cram, and authorities searched
with flashlights for more than an hour in heavy rain but could not
find the missing third of Hedrick's nose.
   Authorities said Alisa Cram is Hedrick's girlfriend.
   The two men and Mrs. Cram met on the highway Monday night,
officials said.
   ``Hedrick thought that Cram was going to beat the girl so he
tried to pull Cram off her,'' sheriff's Detective Judy Herman said.
``Then they began to fight. And that's when he bit him.''
   Cram told sheriff's deputies he was acting in self-defense.
</TEXT>
