Poland's striking workers Wednesday night to settle their local
grievances and end the country's worst labor unrest in seven years.
   Walesa made the appeal hours after meeting with government
leaders on the wave of strikes that began Aug. 16 calling for
higher wages and the legalization of Solidarity.
