Exchange Commission it has received permission to proceed with the
bid and acquire more than 50 percent of Macmillan. Federal
regulators allowed the time period in which they must raise
antitrust concerns to expire last week.
   Maxwell's bid topped a $75-a-share tender offer launched by the
Robert M. Bass Group of Texas, which owns about 9.2 percent of
Macmillan's outstanding shares.
   Bass' overtures prompted Macmillan to devise a restructuring
plan that essentially would split the company in two and pay
shareholders a special dividend. But a court blocked Macmillan from
proceeding with its plan.
   The publishing company, which is appealing the court order,
indicated recently it might sweeten its restructuring proposal but
did not unveil any details.
   Macmillan's shares consistently have traded above the $80 mark.
In afternoon trading on the New York Stock Exchange, Macmillan was
off $1.37{ at $82.24 a share.
