<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   08-31 0153</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Little Changed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London Stock Exchange edged lower
Wednesday after a quiet session as players found little reason to
alter their positions.
   ``We've seen a few nibbles in the cheap stocks but otherwise
there's been no real direction,'' one equity salesman said.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index fell 1.2
points, or 0.06 percent, to finish at 1753.6.
   The Dow Jones industrial average was off 1.78 points at 2036.45
as London trading drew to a close, but market watchers said Wall
Street's mediocre performance was not moving London equities.
   Dealers said concern still lingered over rising global interest
rates and the growing British trade deficit, although these fears
provided more of a backdrop than a stimulus to Wednesday's session.
   On the whole, they said there was little news to guide the
market away from its summer torpor.
</TEXT>
