<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Knight-Ridder-Lockheed     08-31 0132</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Knight-Ridder-Lockheed,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Knight-Ridder Complete's Purchase of Lockheed Subsidiary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Knight-Ridder Inc. completed its $353 million
purchase of Lockheed Corp.'s Dialog Information Services Inc.
Wednesday, the two companies announced.
   Dialog maintains the world's largest computer-based data bank,
with more than 320 databases serving 92,000 subscribers in 86
countries. The company, headquartered in Palo Alto, Calif., had
revenue of $98.1 million in 1987, earning an income of $9.2 million.
   Dialog's international communications network, known as DialNet,
now serves 53 cities in North America as well as London and Tokyo.
   Knight-Ridder publishes 30 daily newspapers, owns and operates
eight network television stations and is engaged in cable
television operations, newsprint production and business
information services.
   The company's various information services reach nearly 100
million people worldwide. Its 1987 revenue totaled $2.1 billion.
</TEXT>
